      <abstract displayLabel="Abstract">The HIPAA Security Rule focuses on safeguarding electronic protected
                health information (ePHI) held or maintained by regulated entities. The ePHI that a
                regulated entity creates, receives, maintains, or transmits must be protected
                against reasonably anticipated threats, hazards, and impermissible uses and/or
                disclosures. This publication provides practical guidance and resources that can be
                used by regulated entities of all sizes to safeguard ePHI and better understand the
                security concepts discussed in the HIPAA Security Rule.</abstract>
